  <channel>
    <title>CKAN: Ticket #1387: Not specifying a protocol in dataset url causes broken link to be served on dataset view page</title>
    <link>http://localhost/ticket/1387</link>
    <description>&lt;p&gt;
If a user enters a url with no protocol (eg: www.data.gov.uk) in the 'url' field of a dataset, a broken link is created on the view page.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
CKAN should probably either put in a &lt;a class="ext-link" href="http://"&gt;&lt;span class="icon"&gt;â€‹&lt;/span&gt;http://&lt;/a&gt; if no protocol is given, or validation should fail.
&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
